    {
      "id": "PopularPost114460",
      "post_content": "This is a great card purely for it's surprise factor. You could be completely tapped out, have no blockers and appear completely vulnerable. Then BOOM, you could rebound the damage on their creature, on the player themselves or my personal favorite (if you are playing a multiplayer game) redirect the damage to a random bystander that happens to have low life.   \nI like to use this for spite in Two-Headed Giant. \"Actually, you just did 7 damage to your teammate... good job\" :)",
