    {
      "id": "PopularPost166765",
      "post_content": "This card is amazing. Easily one of my favorite ever printed.  \n  \nIt's so comforting to have it in your hand. It can keep you or your creatures safe from damage, and can kill creatures or even players. But, what makes it awesome is that it's a combat trick that can be used even when you're tapped out, which puts another level onto the game. There's been times I've tapped myself out on purpose while I had a [Razia](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=89061) in hand just so I could have my opponent go for an all out assault, thinking he's got the game won, until I redirect the fatal points of damage from myself to his face, either killing him outright or putting him within reach of a burn spell.  \n  \nIt's just so awesome to pull those kind of surprise victories, and this card let's anyone do it almost too easily.   \n  \nI do wish the art/flavor was a little bit cooler though. ",
      "posted_by": "Asmodi0000",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost166765\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl08_post\">This card is amazing. Easily one of my favorite ever printed.<br/><br/>It's so comforting to have it in your hand. It can keep you or your creatures safe from damage, and can kill creatures or even players. But, what makes it awesome is that it's a combat trick that can be used even when you're tapped out, which puts another level onto the game. There's been times I've tapped myself out on purpose while I had a <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardid=\"89061\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=89061\">Razia</a> in hand just so I could have my opponent go for an all out assault, thinking he's got the game won, until I redirect the fatal points of damage from myself to his face, either killing him outright or putting him within reach of a burn spell.<br/><br/>It's just so awesome to pull those kind of surprise victories, and this card let's anyone do it almost too easily. <br/><br/>I do wish the art/flavor was a little bit cooler though. </span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl08_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl08_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '166765'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy18984\">Asmodi0000</span>\r\n                                (6/5/2011 10:03:34 PM)\r\n                            </di